= Chapter 21 Hexapods

== Subphylum Hexapoda

- **Characteristics**:
  - Named for the presence of **six legs**.
  - All legs are **uniramous**.
  - Three tagmata: **head**, **thorax**, and **abdomen**.
  - Appendages on head and thorax; abdominal appendages reduced or absent.
- **Classes**:
  - **Entognatha**: Small group; bases of mouthparts enclosed within the head capsule (entognathous).
    - Orders: Protura, Diplura, Collembola (springtails).
  - **Insecta**: Enormous class; bases of mouthparts lie outside the head capsule (ectognathous).
    - Pterygotes (winged) and Apterygotes (wingless).

